I have to agree with TheMightyMcB - I never saw the original draft of this, so I couldn't really compare, but the twist really does work best right at the end here. Once you see it, you look back and see that although these animals are weird and definitely not normal as we'd understand it, they're not really that anomalous when compared to the weird shit that already exists in nature. I also really liked the way this plays on how dinosaurs are often misunderstood based on our initially faulty understanding of fossils (scales v feathers dawn of justice, for example).

+1!







